value.0: I doubt you would be very interested in me. Not too much to tell, but I guess I could share a bit. I'm a druid and have been a member of this grove for about twenty years now. I used to be the second-in-command around here.
Yes, there is. My daughter was part of the expedition of druids that went missing. They were on a mission to find out what's wrong with the Spirit of the Wood, you see.
Her name is Bree. I would go myself, but I must protect the remaining druids at this camp. I will offer you a sum of gold if you can find her... whatever her fate may be.
That's understandable. Just please keep an eye out for a young woman.
Thank you. You bring an old man hope. I await both you, and hopefully, my daughter's safe return.
I will let you know if I come across her.
